events.name: Golden State Warriors at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant looked good as new against his old team, Kyrie Irving was even better and the Brooklyn Nets emphatically kicked off the Steve Nash era with a 125-99 victory over the Golden State Warriors on Tuesday night in the NBA's season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant returns with 22 and a 125-99 Nets rout of Warriors

events.name: LA Clippers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: - Paul George scored 26 of his 33 points in the second half, Kawhi Leonard added 26 points and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied past the Los Angeles Lakers on the NBA champions' ring ceremony night for a 116-109 victory Tuesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: George's 33 sends Clippers past Lakers 116-109 on ring night
